h3. Summary

JS console errors are thrown when displaying all Jira boards if ad-blocking extensions is installed in a browser.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Install an ad-blocking extension in a browser.
 # Go to Boards -> View all boards

h3. Expected Result

Boards are displayed correctly, no errors are logged in JS console.
h3. Actual Result

Errors are loggged:
{code:java}
Uncaught TypeError: Cannot read property 'appendChild' of null 
    at i.handleJsException (batch.js:3) {code}
{code:java}
Uncaught ReferenceError: ace is not defined
    at ManageRapidViews.jspa:155
{code}
{code:java}
GET https://ace-cdn.atlassian.com/stp/current/analytics/js/atl-analytics.min.js net::ERR_BLOCKED_BY_CLIENT{code}
h3. Workarounds

Disable AdBlock or add an exception.

h4. Summary
Scroll option is not available when the *Issues in Epic* list (on issue view page) exceeds issue page

h4. Steps to reproduce
# Add issues in epic on an issue. 
# Minimize the browser size
# Click **Issues in Epic* option gear icon
 !screenshot-1.png|thumbnail! 
# Some options will not be visible

h4. Expected Result
User can scroll to view the hidden options

h4. Actual Result
Scrolling is not possible

h4. Suggestion
JIRA should have scrolling option within the *Issues in Epic* list 

h4.Workaround
Add the following to Jira's [Announcement Banner|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiraserver075/configuring-an-announcement-banner-935390981.html]:
{code}
<style type="text/css">

div#actions_10401_drop {
    overflow: scroll;
    height: 600px;
}

div#actions_10401_drop::before {
    content: "This menu is scrollable";
    text-align: center;
    font-style: italic;
    display: block;
    color: navy;
    font-weight: bold;
    margin-top: 2px;
}

</style>
{code}

(!) The problem here is that the workaround needs to be applied to each and every option button as each button has a unique id eg. actions_10401_drop

To find the id :
# Open the Developer Tools option 
# Select the Elements bar
# Open the drop down
# Select an element on the page to inspect it 
# Here we can see that the id is actions_10401_drop
#  !screenshot-2.png|thumbnail! 
# Replace the id on the announcement banner script accordingly after "div#".

h3. Problem 
Chrome 57+ has new functionality _XSS_AUDITOR_: detects unusual code on this page and blockes it to protect your personal information (for example, passwords, phone numbers, and credit cards). 

h3. +Steps to reproduce+
# Access JIRA using Chrome browser
# Go to Announcement Banner
# Enter a script e.g.:
{code}
<script>
 function() {
   var testVar = "/rest/api/2.0/issue";

   function testScript ($field, testParam) {
     if (!testParam || testParam.length === 0) {
       testFunc($field);
     }
   }
 }
</script>
{code}
# Click Set Banner

h3. +Expected behavior+
Chrome displays no error

h3. +Actual behavior+
Chrome displays an error page warning that the used script might contain unusual code: *ERR_BLOCKED_BY_XSS_AUDITOR*  
!script.jpg|thumbnail!

h3. +Notes+
# Despite the error page:
#* The script is saved successfully and works as intended
#* Other JIRA pages can be accessed normally and going back to Announcement Banner page shows no problem
# Firefox doesn't display an error page

See related pages regarding to Chrome:
* https://stackoverflow.com/questions/43249998/chrome-err-blocked-by-xss-auditor-details
* https://www.bmyers.com/public/Bypassing-the-XSS-AUDITOR-error-in-Chrome.cfm

As a Jira admin, I'd like to request an improvement in the error message below:

{noformat}
Cannot create issue due to invalid license: [Sorry, you can't create any issues right now, as you need to have access to a JIRA application to be able to create issues. To gain application access you need to be a member of a group assigned to an application.
{noformat}

This message is being thrown when Jira is receiving an error from the mail server which is not accurate with the current situation.
